# Pokrovskoye, Republic of Dagestan

}}
Pokrovskoye (; , Åžovde) is a rural locality (a selo) and the administrative center of Pokrovsky Selsoviet, Khasavyurtovsky District, Republic of Dagestan, Russia. Population:  There are 61 streets.
Geography
Pokrovskoye is situated 12&nbsp;km northeast of Khasavyurt (the district's administrative centre) by road. Batayurt is the nearest rural locality.
